In right triangle $JKL$, angle $J$ measures 60 degrees and angle $K$ measures 30 degrees. When drawn, the angle bisectors of angles $J$ and $K$ intersect at a point $M$. What is the measure of obtuse angle $JMK$?

[asy]
import geometry;
import olympiad;
unitsize(0.8inch);
dotfactor = 3;
defaultpen(linewidth(1pt)+fontsize(10pt));

pair J,K,L,M,U,V;

J = (0,0);
K = (1,2);
L = (1,0);

draw(J--K--L--cycle);
draw(rightanglemark(J,L,K,5));

label("$J$",J,W);
label("$K$",K,N);
label("$L$",L,E);

U = (1,2/3);
V = (2/(2+sqrt(3)),0);

draw(J--U);
draw(K--V);

M = intersectionpoint(J--U,K--V);
dot("M",M,NW);
[/asy]

The point $A(3,3)$ is reflected across the $x$-axis to $A^{'}$. Then $A^{'}$ is translated two units to the left to $A^{''}$. The coordinates of $A^{''}$ are $(x,y)$. What is the value of $x+y$? [asy]
draw((-7,0)--(7,0),linewidth(1),Arrows);
draw((0,-7)--(0,7),linewidth(1),Arrows);

for(int i=-5; i<0; ++i)
{

draw((i,-.5)--(i,.5),linewidth(1));
}

for(int i=1; i<6; ++i)
{

draw((i,-.5)--(i,.5),linewidth(1));
}

for(int i=-5; i<0; ++i)
{

draw((-.5,i)--(.5,i),linewidth(1));
}

for(int i=-5; i<0; ++i)
{

draw((-.5,-i)--(.5,-i),linewidth(1));
}

label("$x$", (8,0));
label("$y$", (0,8));

[/asy]

